Summary: This section details the methods available for the SkeletonModification2DTwoBoneIK class, focusing on setting and getting bone indices and NodePaths for the two bones involved in the IK chain.

Methods
* get_joint_one_bone2d_node() → NodePath: Returns the NodePath of the first bone in the IK chain.
* get_joint_one_bone_idx() → int: Returns the index of the first bone in the IK chain.
* get_joint_two_bone2d_node() → NodePath: Returns the NodePath of the second bone in the IK chain.
* get_joint_two_bone_idx() → int: Returns the index of the second bone in the IK chain.
* set_joint_one_bone2d_node(bone2d_node: NodePath) → void: Sets the NodePath of the first bone in the IK chain.
* set_joint_one_bone_idx(bone_idx: int) → void: Sets the index of the first bone in the IK chain.
* set_joint_two_bone2d_node(bone2d_node: NodePath) → void: Sets the NodePath of the second bone in the IK chain.
* set_joint_two_bone_idx(bone_idx: int) → void: Sets the index of the second bone in the IK chain.
