Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodification2dtwoboneik.rst
Summary: This section details the methods for getting and setting the bone nodes and their indices for the TwoBoneIK modification in Godot Engine.

Method: get_joint_one_bone2d_node() → NodePath
Returns the Bone2D node that is being used as the first bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: get_joint_one_bone_idx() → int
Returns the index of the Bone2D node that is being used as the first bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: get_joint_two_bone2d_node() → NodePath
Returns the Bone2D node that is being used as the second bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: get_joint_two_bone_idx() → int
Returns the index of the Bone2D node that is being used as the second bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: set_joint_one_bone2d_node(bone2d_node: NodePath) → void
Sets the Bone2D node that is being used as the first bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: set_joint_one_bone_idx(bone_idx: int) → void
Sets the index of the Bone2D node that is being used as the first bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: set_joint_two_bone2d_node(bone2d_node: NodePath) → void
Sets the Bone2D node that is being used as the second bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.

Method: set_joint_two_bone_idx(bone_idx: int) → void
Sets the index of the Bone2D node that is being used as the second bone in the TwoBoneIK modification.